You can use variables in Actian 4GL select statements by prefixing them with a colon:
```4gl
DEFINE var1 CHAR(20);
LET var1 = 'value';
SELECT col1, col2 FROM table WHERE col3 = :var1;
```

The syntax for the alter group statement is:
```4gl
alter group group_id {, group_id}
add users (user_id {, user_id}) | drop users (user_id {, user_id}) | drop all;
```

You can insert multiple rows from an array using a loop:
```4gl
i = 1;
while i <= emptable.LastRow do
    repeated insert into employee(name, age, salary)
    values(:emptable[i].name,
           :emptable[i].age,
           :emptable[i].salary);
    i = i + 1;
endwhile;
```
